Class LinkedTypeGraph<V>

java.lang.Object
nl.naturalis.common.x.collection.ImmutableMap<Class<?>,V>
nl.naturalis.common.collection.LinkedTypeGraph<V>
Type Parameters:
V - The type of the values in the Map
All Implemented Interfaces:
Map<Class<?>,V>, TypeMap<V>
public final class LinkedTypeGraph<V> extends ImmutableMap<Class<?>,V>
A TypeMap that stores its entries in a data structure similar to the one used by TypeGraph, but is sensitive to the order in which the types are inserted into the map. Thus, if you expect, for example, String.class to be requested often compared to the other types, it pays to add that type first.

The key set provides a depth-first view of the type hierarchy.
